    "body": "<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Managed services such as Amazon RDS cannot be monitored with the Connectivity monitoring rule.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As an alternative method, we recommend that you check whether the host on which the agent is installed can connect to the managed service using a plugin like the following.</span>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\">\n<a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/tree/master/check-tcp\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-tcp</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"3\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Confirm whether or not you can connect to the TCP port of the target managed service</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"3\">\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">See </span><a href=\"https://mackerel.io/docs/entry/howto/check/tcp\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Running checks on TCP servers - Mackerel Help</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for more information</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are also check plugins that specialize in various middleware and protocols. Consider the following according to your target managed service (consult the README of each plugin for details)</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br></span>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\"><a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/tree/master/check-mysql\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-mysql</span></a></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\"><a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/tree/master/check-postgresql\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-postgresql</span></a></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\"><a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/tree/master/check-postgresql\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-redis</span></a></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\"><a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/tree/master/check-http\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-http</span></a></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"2\"><a href=\"https://github.com/mackerelio/go-check-plugins/blob/master/check-smtp\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">check-smtp</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>For reference</strong></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><a href=\"https://support.mackerel.io/hc/en-us/articles/360040107831\" target=\"_self\">What kind of configuration is Mackerel's connectivity monitoring working with?</a></strong></span></li>\n</ul>"
